LOCATION:Online
SUMMARY:Agentic AI Strategies and Applications
DESCRIPTION:Cohort 1:&#160\;June 16 to July 9\, 2026 with live sessions f
 rom Noon to 1:30pm ET every Tuesday and Thursday.&#160\;No asynchronous m
 aterial outside of the live class sessions.  While live attendance is rec
 ommended\, it is not required as the live sessions will be recorded and m
 ade available after each session.  You will need to complete a quiz after
  each session which will require you to have attended live or watched the
  recording in order to pass. You will be given multiple attempts per quiz
  and your highest score is kept.Delivery: Fully online. Live sessions hel
 d via Zoom at scheduled times. Live sessions will be recorded if you cann
 ot attend during the scheduled time.Program Format: Approximately 12 hour
 s total\, delivered over 4 weeks. Each week includes two live\, instructo
 r-led 90-minute sessions with an auto-graded quiz after each live session
 .  Kelley faculty and industry experts will lead you through real-world b
 usiness cases\, simulations\, and hands-on low/no-code exercises as you b
 uild the ability to identify opportunities\, develop agentic workflows\, 
 and evaluate outcomes based on business impact.  Agentic AI Strategies an
 d Applications is designed to equip you with practical skills to immediat
 ely improve productivity using AI. This program focuses on autonomous AI 
 agents—systems that can take goals\, break them into steps\, use tools\
 , and get work executed with minimal human intervention.  The program beg
 ins with essential foundations in modern AI and foundation models (includ
 ing large language models that power agentic workflows)\, presented in an
  accessible way for non-technical professionals. From there\, you will le
 arn to map workflows\, select the right tools\, and translate complex pro
 blems into structured agentic solutions.  The Kelley Agentic AI Certifica
 te Program will be designed and delivered by faculty whose combination of
  current agentic AI instruction\, applied industry experience\, and execu
 tive level teaching clearly differentiates Kelley from other potential pr
 oviders. Together\, the faculty ensure the program reflects both how agen
 tic AI is shaping business today and how professional teams can apply it 
 to build real solutions and drive measurable productivity gains.Global Au
 thority in Enterprise AI Strategy: Dr. Sagar Samtani is a preeminent glob
 al expert in applied AI and cybersecurity. In 2024-2025\, he served as th
 e Director of the AI for Business Intelligence Research Center at Taiwan 
 Semiconductor Manufacturing Company (TSMC)\, the world's most critical se
 miconductor manufacturer. His unique background in guiding enterprise-wid
 e AI strategies for global leaders ensures that this program delivers ins
 ights into connecting AI innovation with large-scale business intelligenc
 e and secure operational workflows.Pioneering Research in Autonomous Syst
 ems: Dr. Jinjing Zhang is a leading agentic AI researcher focused on the 
 intersection of human decision-making and autonomous systems. As the arch
 itect of the #1-ranked Kelley Direct MBA course on Agentic AI\, she bring
 s cutting-edge frameworks for governance\, autonomous deployment\, and en
 terprise-scale use cases.Week 1 — Foundations: What AI is and how it ev
 olved\; non-technical introduction to large language models\; chatbot vs.
  agent\; identifying AI use cases in your organizationWeek 2 — Autonomo
 us Agents: How autonomous agents work\; delegating tasks with context\, i
 nstructions\, and guardrails\; evaluating agent output and knowing when t
 o override\; live demo building an autonomous agentWeek 3 — Building Ag
 entic Systems: How agents use tools and connect to external systems\; kno
 wledge grounding and giving agents access to your data\; memory and multi
 -step workflows\; live demo of an end-to-end agentic workflowWeek 4 — E
 nterprise Reality: Deploying agentic AI in organizations\; governance\, s
 ecurity\, and privacy considerations\; measuring ROI and business impact\
 ; wrap-up discussionCertificate and Digital Badge: Awarded upon completin
 g all pre-recorded modules\, passing all weekly quizzes\, and participati
 on in the live (and on-demand) sessions.Discount pricing is available for
  IU staff\, students and alumni\, as well as partners and companies sendi
 ng three or more participants. Contact us at kelleypd@iu.edu (mailto:%20k
 elleypd@iu.edu) for related discount codes to apply at check out.
